items.abstract:
<jats:p>In the article I wonder about the reasons for the growing popularity of the postapocalyptic
works in the pop culture of the early 21st century. The world after the collapse
of the Western civilization is created in various literary, film and photographic forms, the
examples of which I present in my study. The alternative post-apocalyptic reality is the postindustrial
reality, archaized and non-anthropocentric. The technological regress presented in
the works is based on imaginings of the end and is analogous to the fall of humanity among
those people who survived after the “end” or were born afterwards. In the post-apocalyptic
works of the turn of the 20th and 21st centuries it can be noticed that the authors of the vision
of world “after to end” abandoned an extremely negative tone.

</jats:p>
